# Code Quality Standard (SonarQube Aligned)

## Purpose
Use SonarQube-style quality gates as the common code quality baseline.

## Scope
- Applies to all Go code and tests in this repository.
- Required for new features, refactors, and bug fixes.

## Quality Gate (Team Baseline)
- No new blocker/critical issues.
- No new security hotspots left unreviewed.
- No duplicated logic without clear reason.
- Keep functions small and cohesive (avoid excessive cognitive complexity).
- New behavior must include tests.

## Coding Rules
- Prefer clear, intention-revealing names over abbreviations.
- Keep handlers thin; business flow stays in use cases.
- Avoid deep nesting; return early on invalid paths.
- Avoid giant files; split by responsibility when growth increases complexity.
- Remove dead code and commented-out legacy blocks.

## Reliability Rules
- Always handle returned errors; do not ignore silently.
- Wrap/contextualize errors where needed for diagnosability.
- Apply timeouts and retries explicitly for I/O boundaries.
- Keep side effects explicit and testable.

## Test Rules
- Unit tests for use case logic and critical branching.
- Add regression tests for fixed bugs.
- Keep tests deterministic (no time/local timezone dependency).
- Use mocks at boundaries, not for pure domain logic.

## Maintainability Rules
- No framework leakage into `domain` and `application` core logic.
- Keep DTO/mapper/handler responsibilities separated.
- Centralize cross-cutting concerns (logging, validation, error handling).

## Review Checklist
- Is complexity reasonable for each function?
- Is duplication minimized?
- Are errors handled and logged properly?
- Are tests covering new paths and failure paths?
- Does code follow existing architecture boundaries?
